  "According to Ohm's law, the current through a resistor equals:": "",
  "I = V/R": "",
  "I = R/V": "",
  "I = VR": "",
  "I = V²/R": "",
  "Ohm's law: I = V/R, where V is the voltage across the resistor and R is its resistance. Higher voltage or lower resistance means more current.": "",
